  <fr:p>To identify two witnesses <fr:tex>\phi , \phi '  \colon   \mathchoice { \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \textstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y:A \right ) \mathclose {} } }{ \scriptscriptstyle \prod _{ \mathopen {} \left ( x,y:A \right ) \mathclose {} } } x = y</fr:tex> that <fr:tex>A</fr:tex> is a <fr:link
href="erct-001I.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-001I">proposition</fr:link>, it suffices via <fr:ref
addr="erct-0015"
href="erct-0015.xml"
taxon="Axiom"></fr:ref> to exhibit a double homotopy in <fr:tex>A</fr:tex> identifying each <fr:tex>\phi  xy</fr:tex> with <fr:tex>\phi 'xy</fr:tex>. By <fr:ref
addr="erct-001L"
href="erct-001L.xml"
taxon="Lemma"></fr:ref>, this follows from our assumption that <fr:tex>A</fr:tex> is a <fr:link
href="erct-001I.xml"
type="local"
addr="erct-001I">proposition</fr:link>.</fr:p>
